Section 1:
1 L.D. 1731
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 TRANSPORTATION
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 677, L.D. 1731, “An Act to Increase the
10 Influence of the Maine State Ferry Advisory Board on the Funding and Operations of the
11 Maine State Ferry Service”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act to Enhance the Effectiveness of the Maine State Ferry Advisory Board'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
15 following:
16 'Sec. 1. 23 MRSA §4302, as amended by PL 1997, c. 643, Pt. QQ, §2, is further
17 amended to read:
18 §4302. Membership
19 The membership of the board consists of one person from each of the island
20 municipalities and plantations serviced by the Maine State Ferry System and 3 4 members
21 appointed by the Commissioner of Transportation, one of which must be a municipal
22 officer from Rockland, Lincolnville or Tremont. The members Each member representing
23 the an island municipalities and plantations shall municipality or plantation must be the
24 chief administrative official of the island or a current member of the governing body of the
25 island and must be appointed by the municipal officers of the member's municipality or by
26 the assessors of the member's plantation and all. All members shall serve a term of office
27 of 2 years. Each island municipality shall appoint one alternate member to the board. In
28 the absence of the island's primary representative, its alternate may represent the island at
29 all board meetings. Vacancies in membership must be filled in the same manner as the
30 original appointment.
31 Sec. 2. 23 MRSA §4303, sub-§3 is enacted to read:
32 3. Public meetings. Meetings of the board must be public meetings as provided by
33 Title 1, section 403.
34 Sec. 3. 23 MRSA §4304, as amended by PL 1985, c. 253, is further amended to
35 read:
Page 1 - 132LR2108(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 677, L.D. 1731
1 §4304. Duties
2 The board shall advise the Department of Transportation on matters relating to the
3 Maine State Ferry Service and shall submit to the Commissioner of Transportation and to
4 the joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over transportation
5 matters by December 15th an annual report, which shall must include recommendations
6 for change to the Maine State Ferry Service and comments upon the present and future
7 needs of that service. The Department of Transportation shall also prepare and submit an
8 annual report by December 15th to the board, to the island municipalities and plantations
9 served by the Maine State Ferry Service and to the joint standing committee of the
10 Legislature having jurisdiction over transportation matters. The report must include the
11 operating and capital costs, past and projected costs, significant successes and challenges
12 and policy issues of the Maine State Ferry Service. Written reports and comments shall
13 must be available to the public.
14 The board, in consultation with the Commissioner of Transportation, shall name ferry
15 terminals and ferries constructed for and maintained by the Department of Transportation
16 to operate as part of the Maine State Ferry Service.'
17 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
18 number to read consecutively.
19 SUMMARY
2200 This amendment, which is a minority report of the committee, replaces the bill and
2211 changes the title. The amendment does the following.
22 1. It increases, from 3 to 4, the number of members of the Maine State Ferry Advisory
23 Board appointed by the Commissioner of Transportation and requires one of those
24 members of the board to be a municipal officer from Rockland, Lincolnville or Tremont.
25 2. It requires a member of the board representing an island municipality or plantation,
26 who is appointed by the municipal officers of the member's municipality or by the assessors
27 of the member's plantation, to be the chief administrative official of the island or a current
28 member of the governing body of the island.
29 3. It requires the board to submit an annual report to the joint standing committee of
30 the Legislature having jurisdiction over transportation matters, in addition to the
31 Commissioner of Transportation.
32 4. It requires the Department of Transportation to prepare and submit a report to the
33 board, the island municipalities and plantations served by the Maine State Ferry Service
34 and the joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over transportation
35 matters. The report must include the operating and capital costs, past and projected costs,
36 significant successes and challenges and policy issues of the Maine State Ferry Service.
37 5. It requires meetings of the board to be public meetings as provided by the Maine
38 Revised Statutes, Title 1, section 403.
3399 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
4400 (See attached)
